Lucas de la Pena

Use this to run the code:
python PhotoExplorer.py -a -g -rows numrows -cols numcols -t type indir outdir


This Program Browes through all images in a directory, displays them one at a time in an OpenCV window. Using the options you can change the size, convert to grayscale, and can save in a new format

-a : preserve aspect ratio when resizing

-g : Save output as grayscale

-rows : Max window height

-cols : Max window width

-t : Output file type (jpg/tif/bmp/png)

indir : Folder with input images

outdir : folder to save processed images

Sample execution:
python PhotoExplorer.py -a -g -rows 480 -cols 640 -t jpg dir outdir

installs:
pip install screen info
pip install opencv-python


